Title: UC Berkeley Digital Library Project
Body: Date: Wed, 20 Nov 1996 19:25:45 GMT Server: NCSA/1.5 Content-type: text/html Last-modified: Wed, 06 Nov 1996 20:20:12 GMT Content-length: 2962 UC Berkeley Digital Library Project The UC Berkeley Digital Library project is a 4-year, $4 million research project that includes faculty, staff, and students in the Computer Science Division, the School of Information Management & Systems, and the Research Program in Environmental Planning & Geographic Information Systems, as well as participation from several state and local agencies and industrial partners.
